Key Match Events: Will Smith hit a tying, two-run homer in the seventh inning.
Shohei Ohtani hit an RBI single and advanced to second on a throwing error by Fernando Tatis Jr.
Andy Pages hit a two-run home run in the eighth inning.
Freddie Freeman suffered an injury after colliding with Luis Arráez and the first base bag.
Post-Match Reflections: Manager Dave Roberts expressed pride in his team's resilience and ability to overcome adversity.
Shohei Ohtani expressed happiness about clinching the title.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Dodgers clinched the NL West title with a 7-2 victory over the Padres.
A sellout crowd of 52,433, including retired Dodgers star Manny Ramirez, attended the game.
Both teams had already clinched postseason berths before this game.
